org.pragmaticminds.crunch.api.trigger

Class TriggerEvaluationFunction<T extends Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pragmaticminds.crunch.api.trigger.TriggerEvaluationFunction<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, EvaluationFunction<T>

    public class TriggerEvaluationFunction<T extends Serializable>
extends Object
implements EvaluationFunction<T>
    Simplifies the way to implement EvaluationFunction for typical tasks. The Supplier pre evaluates the incoming data, so that the TriggerStrategy can decide if further processing is required in the TriggerHandler. The TriggerHandler than generates Event resulting from the incoming data. The optional EventFilter than filters the resulting Events before they are passed to the next processing step. eval(EvaluationContext) | |-- MRecord | TriggerStrategy | |-- MRecord | (TriggerHandler) | |-- List of Event | (EventFilter | |-- List of Event | EvaluationContext::collect(Event)
